Kepware Guide
1
Open your browser and navigate to: "https://IP_Data_Collector/". You can also use
the a4conf icon on the Data Collector desktop.
2
Click "Data-Collector" within the main menu.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 2
3
Select "Kepware".
4
The "Machine Serial" field allows you to enter a machine serial number and add it
to a list if required. This is useful if you are creating IoT gateways to send data to
ThingWorx since you can directly indicate the remote thing on which the tags
contained in that IoT Gateway will be sent.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 3
5
Click the "Add" button to the right of the "Machine serial" field to add the serial
number to the serial number list.
6
The "Create IoT Gateway" section allows you to create different types of IoT
Gateways. To learn more about this section, there are specific sections for each
type of Gateway you can create.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 4
7
Move to "Kepware configuration".
8
You can "Download" or "Upload " the Kepware project as a JSON file.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 5
9
Click the "Load default project" button to load the latest a4GATE Kepware default
project released.
10
If the load is successful, a banner will appear saying "Kepware default project
loaded successfully" and it will create a Kepware project backup at the specified
path.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 6
11
Click the "Reload" button to reload the Kepware runtime.
12
Move to "License".
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 7
13
Kepware mode is set by default to "Trial mode". When licence will be installed by
a4GATE team, you have to select the checkbox to change the Kepware mode to
"Licence mode".
14
Move to "Machines Configured".
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 8
15
This section contains all the informations about Kepware channels. By clicking on
a channel, you can see its devices.
16
By clicking on the different devices, you can view detailed information about its
configuration, such as the IP address, port number, connection status, the driver
type and the last timestamp the status of the connection has been checked.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 9
17
Click the "Apply" button to apply the new configurations.
